———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
This is minsoehan's dash scripts collection mainly consist of
"infonoti" "mshcns" "mshcaudio" "mshcsbl" and others
———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
cd to mshii folder then run installii as follows;
    $ cd ~/path/mshii
    $ ./installii
It will creat symlink named as "ii" in $PATH to ./infonotiswitch.sh

The structure is as follows;

ii (symlink in $PATH)
 |
 |——masterii
 |  |
 |  |——infonotitoggle.sh——iwaited/audiomutestate,volumelevel,screenbl
 |     |
 |     |——infonotiloop.sh——inotifywait——iwaited/*
 |     |——loopswitch.sh
 |        |
 |        |——datetimeloop.sh——iwaited/datetime
 |        |——batstateloop.sh——iwaited/batstatus,batlevel
 |        |——netstateloop.sh——iwaited/constate,curessid,curipaddr
 |        
 |——infonotiswitch.sh——batnotitoggle.sh——iwaited/bnstate
    $ ii bnt|bntoggle (only if required)
    $ ii bnt enable
    $ ii bnt disable
———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
"mshcns"
    $ mshcns
following on screen instructions
———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
"mshcaudio"
    $ mshcaudio mutetoggle
    $ mshcaudio volup
    $ mshcaudio voldown
———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
"mshcsbl"
    $ mshcsbl up
    $ mshcsbl down
———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
"fwmn"
# fuzzelmn or wofimn
    $ menu [dic|fm|mn1|mn2|mn3]
